mkdfu
-----

A tool to install/uninstall a dual bootloader into a Classic 6G.

Actually it generates a .dfu file that should be injected into iPod using
ipoddfu.py or ipoddfu_c.

TODO: integrate ipoddfu_c with mk6gboot


Usage
-----

mk6gboot <boot file> <output file> [-u]

<boot file> is the code you want to execute (a rockbox bootloader), previously
    scrambled with tools/scramble utility.

<output file> is the resulting DFU file which you'll have to inject into your
    iPod using ipoddfu.py or ipoddfu_c.

-u: generates a DFU uninstaller that removes RB dual bootloader from the iPod
    and it is restored to it's original state (NOR).

command line example:

 ~/rockbox/rbutil/mk6gboot$ ./mk6gboot \
        ../../build/bootloader-ipod6g.ipod dualboot-installer-ipod6g.dfu
 ~/ipoddfu$ sudo python ./ipoddfu.py /path/to/dualboot-installer-ipod6g.dfu

When the .dfu is loaded it emits a 2000Hz/100ms 'alive' tone. When RB loader
is successfully installed then 1000Hz/100ms+2000Hz/150ms beep sounds and the
device reboots. If something when bad then 330Hz/500ms tone is emited and
the device reboots. When an intermitent 330Hz tone sounds forever then the
NOR got corrupted and the device must be restored using iTunes (should not
happen).


Supported FW
------------

1.1.2
2.0.4
TODO?: 2.0.1


Dual-Boot
---------

The purpose of this program is to provide dual-boot between the original
firmware and the new (rockbox) firmware.

Actually, when the bootloader starts it emits an 'alive' beep, the button
press check is done 1 second after, then:

  SELECT + MENU: reboot and enter DFU mode
  SELECT + LEFT: enter OF diagnostics
  SELECT + PLAY: enter OF diskmode
  RIGTH: launch emCORE (not tested)
  No button pressed and holdswitch unlocked: launch Rockbox
  Any other combination: launch OF

TODO: Probably we can save a default firmware selection into a PMU memory
register, then define an unique button combination to change the default
firmware selection.


Hacking
-------

See comments in mkdfu.c and dualboot/dualboot.c for more information.
